# Coach Sidekick - Project Overview

## Project Description
Coach Sidekick is a an application that will help coaches to take help from ai during meetings. 

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 15.3.4 with App Router
- **React**: React 19 
- **TypeScript**: Full TypeScript support with strict mode
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 with PostCSS
- **Fonts**: Geist Sans & Geist Mono from Google Fonts
- **Development**: Turbopack for fast development builds
- **Linting**: ESLint with Next.js configuration

## Project Structure
```
src/
├── app/                    # Next.js App Router directory
│   ├── layout.tsx         # Root layout component
│   ├── page.tsx           # Home page component
│   ├── globals.css        # Global styles with Tailwind
│   └── favicon.ico        # App favicon
public/                     # Static assets
├── file.svg, globe.svg, etc.
```

## Key Configuration Files
- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Dependencies and scripts
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration with path aliases
- [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts) - Next.js configuration
- [eslint.config.mjs](mdc:eslint.config.mjs) - ESLint rules
- [postcss.config.mjs](mdc:postcss.config.mjs) - PostCSS for Tailwind

## Development Commands
```bash
npm run dev      # Start development server with Turbopack
npm run build    # Build for production
npm run start    # Start production server
npm run lint     # Run ESLint
```

## Path Aliases
The project uses TypeScript path aliases configured in [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json):
- `@/*` maps to `./src/*` for clean imports
